library(data.table)
#library(ggpubr)
library(MetBrewer)
library(kinship2)
library(viridis)
library(dplyr) #my import 
library(visNetwork)
library(grid)
library(ggplot2)
#library(plotly)
library(ggnewscale)
library(shiny)
#library(htmlwidgets)
library(shinylive)



############################################################################
# __________________________________________________________________________
# READ AND PROCESS NAMU DATA 
# __________________________________________________________________________
# Verzeichnis des aktuell ausgef√ºhrten Skripts ermitteln und als Arbeitsverzeichnis festlegen

#setwd(dirname(rstudioapi::getActiveDocumentContext()$path))

df.achaeo <- fread("All_data_process_LRA_120524.txt", header=T, sep="\t")
# add clustering from network:
community <- fread("Network_clusters.txt") %>%
  rename("Network_clusters"="community")
community$Network_clusters <- as.character(community$Network_clusters)
df.achaeo <- merge(df.achaeo, community, all.x=T, by.x="Individual_ID", by.y="id")


KIN <- fread("KIN_results_131222.csv", sep="\t")

ID1 <- unlist(lapply(strsplit(unlist(lapply(strsplit(KIN$Pair, "_._"), head, 1)), "[.]"), head, 1))
ID2 <- unlist(lapply(strsplit(unlist(lapply(strsplit(KIN$Pair, "_._"), tail, 1)), "[.]"), head, 1))

KIN$ID1 <- ID1
KIN$ID2 <- ID2

KIN.red <- KIN[!KIN$Relatedness %in% c("Unrelated"),]  %>% 
  select(ID1, ID2, Relatedness, k0)

K3 <- fread("genealogy_K3.txt", header=T)
K1.2.4 <- fread("genealogy_K1.2.B.C2.4B_97GP_19U_5A.txt", header=T)[,-8]
pd <- rbind(K1.2.4, K3)

pedAll <- pedigree(id=pd$id, dadid=pd$father, momid=pd$mother, 
                   sex=pd$sex, famid=pd$ped)

df.achaeo$kin.group <- "Unkown"
df.achaeo[df.achaeo$Individual_ID %in% K1.2.4$id,]$kin.group <- "K1.2.4"
df.achaeo[df.achaeo$Individual_ID %in% K3$id,]$kin.group <- "K3"
df.achaeo$kin.highlight <- df.achaeo$kin.group


couples <- pd %>% dplyr::filter(mother %in% df.achaeo$Individual_ID & !is.na(mother)) %>%
  dplyr::filter(father %in% df.achaeo$Individual_ID & !is.na(father))
couples.curves <- data.frame(
  father=df.achaeo[match(couples$father, df.achaeo$Individual_ID),]$Individual_ID,
  mother=df.achaeo[match(couples$mother, df.achaeo$Individual_ID),]$Individual_ID,
  X_craneo=df.achaeo[match(couples$father, df.achaeo$Individual_ID),]$X_craneo,
  Y_craneo=df.achaeo[match(couples$father, df.achaeo$Individual_ID),]$Y_craneo,
  X_craneo_end=df.achaeo[match(couples$mother, df.achaeo$Individual_ID),]$X_craneo,
  Y_craneo_end=df.achaeo[match(couples$mother, df.achaeo$Individual_ID),]$Y_craneo,
  Layer_father=df.achaeo[match(couples$father, df.achaeo$Individual_ID),]$Layer,
  Layer_mother=df.achaeo[match(couples$mother, df.achaeo$Individual_ID),]$Layer
)
couples.curves$kin.group <- "Unkown"
couples.curves[(couples.curves$mother %in% K1.2.4$id) & (couples.curves$father %in% K1.2.4$id),]$kin.group <- "K1.2.4"
couples.curves[(couples.curves$mother %in% K3$id) & (couples.curves$father %in% K3$id),]$kin.group <- "K3"

kin.curves <- data.frame(
  ID1=df.achaeo[match(KIN.red$ID1, df.achaeo$Individual_ID),]$Individual_ID,
  ID2=df.achaeo[match(KIN.red$ID2, df.achaeo$Individual_ID),]$Individual_ID,
  X_craneo=df.achaeo[match(KIN.red$ID1, df.achaeo$Individual_ID),]$X_craneo,
  Y_craneo=df.achaeo[match(KIN.red$ID1, df.achaeo$Individual_ID),]$Y_craneo,
  X_craneo_xend=df.achaeo[match(KIN.red$ID2, df.achaeo$Individual_ID),]$X_craneo,
  Y_craneo_yend=df.achaeo[match(KIN.red$ID2, df.achaeo$Individual_ID),]$Y_craneo,
  Layer_ID1=df.achaeo[match(KIN.red$ID1, df.achaeo$Individual_ID),]$Layer,
  Layer_ID2=df.achaeo[match(KIN.red$ID2, df.achaeo$Individual_ID),]$Layer,
  relatedness=KIN.red$Relatedness
)
kin.curves$kin.group <- "Unkown"
kin.curves[(kin.curves$ID1 %in% K1.2.4$id) & (kin.curves$ID2 %in% K1.2.4$id),]$kin.group <- "K1.2.4"
kin.curves[(kin.curves$ID1 %in% K3$id) & (kin.curves$ID2 %in% K3$id),]$kin.group <- "K3"
kin.curves <- kin.curves %>%
  filter(X_craneo != X_craneo_xend | Y_craneo != Y_craneo_yend) #my comment: prevent pointing at itself
# Plot parameters:
color.mthap_haplogrep <- c("#C2FFF3", "#16EFD9", "#00BEAA", "#008F7D", "#006253", "#00382D", 
                           "#EAAEB4", "#DD7E88", "#D04E5B","#B12F3C", 
                           "#EC8B5B", "#923C11", "red")
names(color.mthap_haplogrep) <- sort(na.omit(unique(df.achaeo$mthap_haplogrep)))

color.mthap_haplocart <- c("#C2FFF3", "#16EFD9", "#00BEAA", "#008F7D", "#006253", "#00382D", "#5d89e8", "#1b4fbf", "#15288a",
                           "#EAAEB4", "#DD7E88", 
                           "#EC8B5B", "#923C11", "red")
names(color.mthap_haplocart) <- sort(na.omit(unique(df.achaeo$mthap_haplocart)))

color.Ychr_HG_pathPfynder <- c("#394A7F", "#8092C6","#EF476F", "#0A7020", "#12CE3B", "#7CF496")
names(color.Ychr_HG_pathPfynder) <- sort(na.omit(unique(df.achaeo$Ychr_HG_pathPfynder)))
formatted_names <- sapply(names(color.Ychr_HG_pathPfynder), function(x) {
  # Ersetze jedes ';' durch einen Zeilenumbruch '\n'
  gsub(";", "\n", x)
})

# Die formatierten Namen der Legende zuweisen
names(color.Ychr_HG_pathPfynder) <- formatted_names
names(color.Ychr_HG_pathPfynder) <-c("C1b2a","C1b2a1c2a","O2a2b2a2", "S1a1b", "S1a2","S1d;A00") #manuel version, please remove if not correct

colores.network <- c(met.brewer("Signac", 10), rep("gray80", 8))
names(colores.network) <- 1:18



server <- function(input, output) {
  
  ranges <- reactiveValues(x=NULL, y=NULL)
  
  output$plot <- renderPlot({
    
    # Plots _______________________________________________________________
    
    df.achaeo <- df.achaeo %>% filter(!is.na(Layer))
    #removed_rows <- df.achaeo %>% 
    #  filter(is.na(X_craneo) | is.na(Y_craneo) | is.na(.data[[input$varColor]]))
    
    #df.achaeo_filtered <- df.achaeo %>% 
    #  filter(!is.na(X_craneo), !is.na(Y_craneo), !is.na(.data[[input$varColor]]))
    
    #if (nrow(removed_rows) > 0) {
    #  print("The following lines were removed:")
    #  print(removed_rows)
    #}
    
    # Plot archaeological base site:
    p.base <- ggplot(df.achaeo %>% filter(Genetic_Sex %in% req(input$Genetic_Sex))
                     %>% filter(kin.group %in% req(input$kin.group))
                     %>% filter(Genetic.info %in% req(input$Genetic.info)),
                     aes(x=X_craneo, y=Y_craneo, shape=Genetic_Sex))+
      #coord_cartesian(xlim=ranges$x, ylim=ranges$y, expand=T)+
      # add horizontal lines for reference
      #geom_hline(yintercept=unique(df.achaeo$y), color="gray80", alpha=0.4)+
      # plot burials
      geom_point(size=5, alpha=0.3, aes(color=.data[[input$varColor]]))+
      scale_shape_manual(name="Genetic_Sex", values=c(19,15))+
      # set scale of colors depending on the variable to show on the display:
      {if(input$varColor %in% c("Age_continuous", "Age_discontinuous", "Wealth_of_person_continous", "Average_Date ((earlier+later)/2)(1950 as present)", 
                                "Date_Earlier (calBP)", "Date_Later (calBP)","Strontium", "Genetic.info", 
                                paste0("sum_roh>", c(4,8,12,20)), "Ami", "Network_clusters"))
        scale_color_gradientn(colors=met.brewer("Hiroshige", direction = -1))}+
      {if(input$varColor=="mthap_haplogrep")
        scale_color_manual(values=color.mthap_haplogrep)}+
      {if(input$varColor=="Genetic.info")
        scale_color_manual(values=c("gray20", "#6268DD"))}+
      {if(input$varColor=="Genetic.info")
        scale_shape_manual(values=c(19, 19))}+
      {if(input$varColor=="mthap_haplocart")
        scale_color_manual(values=color.mthap_haplocart)}+
      {if(input$varColor=="Ychr_HG_pathPfynder")
        scale_color_manual(values=color.Ychr_HG_pathPfynder)}+
      {if(input$varColor=="Network_clusters")
        scale_color_manual(values=colores.network)}+
      # add labels of the samples:
      geom_text(size=2, aes(label=.data[[input$IDcode]]))+
      xlim(c(min(df.achaeo$X_craneo), max(df.achaeo$X_craneo)))+
      ylim(c(min(df.achaeo$Y_craneo), max(df.achaeo$Y_craneo)))+
      # highlight kin group:
      {if(length(input$kin.highlight>=1)) 
        geom_point(data=df.achaeo %>% filter(kin.highlight %in% req(input$kin.highlight)),
                   size=7, alpha=1, aes(color=.data[[input$varColor]]))}+
      {if(length(input$kin.highlight>=1)) 
        geom_text(data=df.achaeo %>% filter(kin.highlight %in% req(input$kin.highlight)),
                  size=3, fontface="bold", aes(label=.data[[input$IDcode]]))} +
      # select specific samples:
      {if(length(input$ID.genetic>=1)) 
        geom_point(data=df.achaeo %>% filter(ID.genetic %in% req(input$ID.genetic)),
                   size=7, alpha=1, aes(color=.data[[input$varColor]]))}+
      {if(length(input$ID.genetic>=1)) 
        geom_text(data=df.achaeo %>% filter(ID.genetic %in% req(input$ID.genetic)),
                  size=3, fontface="bold", aes(label=.data[[input$IDcode]]))} +
      facet_wrap(~Layer) +
      theme_minimal()+
      coord_fixed()+
      ylab("")+xlab("")+
      theme(strip.text.x=element_text(hjust=0),
            panel.border=element_rect(colour="gray90", fill=NA, size=1),
            axis.text=element_blank(),
            panel.grid.minor=element_blank())
    
    
    
    # add samples without genetic info:
    if(any(input$Genetic.info %in% "No")){
      p.base <- p.base +
        new_scale(new_aes="shape")+
        geom_point(data=subset(df.achaeo, Genetic.info=="No"), aes(shape=Archaeo_sex, color=.data[[input$varColor]]), size=3)+
        scale_shape_manual(name="Archaeo_sex", values=c(1,0,5))
    }
    
    #old position of couples curve
    if (input$couples == "Yes") {
      couples.curves <- couples.curves %>% filter(Layer_father==Layer_mother) %>% dplyr::rename(Layer=Layer_father)
      
      p.base <- p.base +
        new_scale_colour() +
        geom_curve(inherit.aes = FALSE, alpha = 0.3,
                   data = couples.curves %>% filter(kin.group %in% req(input$kin.group)),
                   linewidth = 1, color = "gray50",
                   aes(x = X_craneo, xend = X_craneo_end, y = Y_craneo, yend = Y_craneo_end),
                   curvature = 0.1) +
        facet_wrap(~Layer)
    }
    
    
    
    # Plot relatedness connectors:____
    # Color for relatedness connectors
    color.rel <- c(met.brewer(name="Hokusai1", n=5)[1],met.brewer(name="Hokusai1", n=5)[2], 
                   met.brewer(name="Hokusai1", n=5)[4], met.brewer(name="Hokusai1", n=5)[3])
    names(color.rel) <- unique(kin.curves$relatedness) 
    
    kin.curves <- kin.curves %>% filter(Layer_ID1==Layer_ID2) %>% dplyr::rename(Layer=Layer_ID1)
    
    if(length(input$relatedness>=1)){
      p.kin.curves <- p.base +
        new_scale_colour() +
        geom_curve(inherit.aes=F, alpha=0.3,
                   data=kin.curves %>% filter(relatedness %in% req(input$relatedness))
                   %>% filter(kin.group %in% req(input$kin.group)),
                   aes(x=X_craneo, xend=X_craneo_xend, y=Y_craneo, yend=Y_craneo_yend,
                       color=relatedness, size=relatedness),curvature=0.1)+
        scale_color_manual(values=color.rel)+
        scale_size_manual(values=c(0.8, 0.6, 0.4, 0.3)) +
        facet_wrap(~Layer)
      
      p.kin.curves
    } else {
      p.base
    }
    
  }
  
  )
  
  
  # add information on samples with a click:
  output$click_info <- renderPrint({
    points_near <- nearPoints(df.achaeo, input$plot_click, addDist = TRUE)
    if (nrow(points_near) == 0) {
      cat("Click to show near points.")
    } else {
      print(points_near)
    }
  })
  
  # zoom with brush:
  observeEvent(input$plot_dblclick, {
    brush <- input$plot_brush
    if (!is.null(brush)) {
      ranges$x <- c(brush$xmin, brush$xmax)
      ranges$y <- c(brush$ymin, brush$ymax)
    } else {
      ranges$x <- NULL
      ranges$y <- NULL
    }
  })
  
  
  # __________________________________________________________________________
  # GENEALOGICAL TREES
  # __________________________________________________________________________
  
  # __________________________________________________________________________
  # Define behavior: _________________________________________________________
  
  pd <- merge(pd, df.achaeo, by.x="id", by.y="Individual_ID", all.x=T)
  
  
  # Add colors to plot:
  
  # wealth:
  color_palette_wealth <- met.brewer("Hiroshige", max(na.omit(pd$Wealth_of_person_continuous)))
  pd$col.wealth <- color_palette_wealth[pd$Wealth_of_person_continuous]
  pd[is.na(pd$col.wealth),]$col.wealth <- "gray20"
  
  #n_roh>20:
  color_palette_n_roh_20 <- met.brewer("Hiroshige", max(na.omit(pd$`n_roh>20`))+1)
  pd$`col.n_roh>20` <- "-"
  pd[is.na(pd$`n_roh>20`)]$`col.n_roh>20` <- "gray20"
  pd[pd$`n_roh>20`==0]$`col.n_roh>20` <- color_palette_n_roh_20[1]
  pd[pd$`n_roh>20`!=0]$`col.n_roh>20` <- color_palette_n_roh_20[-1][pd[pd$`n_roh>20`!=0]$`n_roh>20`]
  
  #n_roh>12:
  color_palette_n_roh_12 <- met.brewer("Hiroshige", max(na.omit(pd$`n_roh>12`))+1)
  pd$`col.n_roh>12` <- "-"
  pd[is.na(pd$`n_roh>12`)]$`col.n_roh>12` <- "gray20"
  pd[pd$`n_roh>12`==0]$`col.n_roh>12` <- color_palette_n_roh_12[1]
  pd[pd$`n_roh>12`!=0]$`col.n_roh>12` <- color_palette_n_roh_12[-1][pd[pd$`n_roh>12`!=0]$`n_roh>12`]
  
  #mtDNA
  pd$col.mthap_haplocart <- color.mthap_haplocart[match(pd$mthap_haplocart, names(color.mthap_haplocart))]
  pd[is.na(pd$col.mthap_haplocart),]$col.mthap_haplocart <- "gray20"
  
  pd$col.mthap_haplogrep <- color.mthap_haplogrep[match(pd$mthap_haplogrep, names(color.mthap_haplogrep))]
  pd[is.na(pd$col.mthap_haplogrep),]$col.mthap_haplogrep <- "gray20"
  
  #Y chr:
  pd$col.Ychr <- color.Ychr_HG_pathPfynder[match(pd$Ychr_HG_pathPfynder, names(color.Ychr_HG_pathPfynder))]
  pd[is.na(pd$col.Ychr),]$col.Ychr <- "gray20"
  
  pd.1.2.4 <- pd[match(pedAll[1]$id, pd$id),]
  pd.3 <- pd[match(pedAll[2]$id, pd$id),]
  #pd.5 <- pd[match(pedAll[3]$id, pd$id),]
  
  
  output$plot1 <- renderPlot({
    {if(input$pdColor=="Wealth")
      col=pd.1.2.4$col.wealth
    }
    {if(input$pdColor=="n_roh>20")
      col=pd.1.2.4$`col.n_roh>20`
    }
    {if(input$pdColor=="n_roh>12")
      col=pd.1.2.4$`col.n_roh>12`
    }
    {if(input$pdColor=="Ychr_HG_pathPfynder")
      col=pd.1.2.4$col.Ychr
    }
    {if(input$pdColor=="mthap_haplocart")
      col=pd.1.2.4$col.mthap_haplocart
    }
    {if(input$pdColor=="mthap_haplogrep")
      col=pd.1.2.4$col.mthap_haplogrep
    }
    plot(pedAll[1], affected=pd.1.2.4$avail, symbolsize=.8, cex=.6,
         width=17,col=col)
  })
  
  output$plot2 <- renderPlot({
    {if(input$pdColor=="Wealth")
      col=pd.3$col.wealth
    }
    {if(input$pdColor=="n_roh>20")
      col=pd.3$`col.n_roh>20`
    }
    {if(input$pdColor=="n_roh>12")
      col=pd.3$`col.n_roh>12`
    }
    {if(input$pdColor=="Ychr_HG_pathPfynder")
      col=pd.3$col.Ychr
      
    }
    {if(input$pdColor=="mthap_haplocart")
      col=pd.3$col.mthap_haplocart
      
    }
    {if(input$pdColor=="mthap_haplogrep")
      col=pd.3$col.mthap_haplogrep
    }
    plot(pedAll[2], affected=pd.3$avail, symbolsize=.8, cex=.6,
         width=17,col=col)
  })
  
  output$plot3 <- renderPlot({
    {if(input$pdColor=="Wealth")
      col=pd.5$col.wealth
    }
    {if(input$pdColor=="n_roh>12")
      col=pd.5$`col.n_roh>12`
    }
    {if(input$pdColor=="n_roh>20")
      col=pd.5$`col.n_roh>20`
    }
    {if(input$pdColor=="Ychr_HG_pathPfynder")
      col=pd.5$col.Ychr
    }
    {if(input$pdColor=="mthap_haplocart")
      col=pd.5$col.mthap_haplocart
    }
    {if(input$pdColor=="mthap_haplogrep")
      col=pd.5$col.mthap_haplogrep
    }
    plot(pedAll[3], affected=pd.5$avail, symbolsize=.8, cex=.6,
         width=17,col=col)
  })
  
  output$legend.ped <- renderPlot({
    
    {if(input$pdColor=="Wealth"){
      plot(xlab="", ylab="", xaxt="n", yaxt="n", c(15.8,17), c(1.1,2.1), type = "n",
           axes=F)
      legend_image <- as.raster(matrix(color_palette_wealth), ncol=1)
      rasterImage(legend_image, 15.8, 1.1, 16.2, 2.1)
      text(cex=0.8, x=16.25, adj=c(0,0.5), y=seq(2.1,1.1,l=5), labels = seq(
        min(na.omit(pd$Wealth_of_person_continuous)),
        max(na.omit(pd$Wealth_of_person_continuous)),l=5))}
    }
    
    {if(input$pdColor=="n_roh>20"){
      plot(xlab="", ylab="", xaxt="n", yaxt="n", c(15.8,17), c(1.1,2.1), type = "n",
           axes=F)
      legend_image <- as.raster(matrix(color_palette_n_roh_20), ncol=1)
      rasterImage(legend_image, 15.8, 1.1, 16.2, 2.1, oma=c(0,0,0,0), mar=c(0,0,0,0))
      text(cex=0.8, x=16.25, adj=c(0,0.5), y=seq(2.1,1.1,l=5), labels = seq(
        min(na.omit(pd$`n_roh>20`)),
        max(na.omit(pd$`n_roh>20`)),l=5))}
    }
    
    {if(input$pdColor=="n_roh>12"){
      plot(xlab="", ylab="", xaxt="n", yaxt="n", c(15.8,17), c(1.1,2.1), type = "n",
           axes=F)
      legend_image <- as.raster(matrix(color_palette_n_roh_12), ncol=1)
      rasterImage(legend_image, 15.8, 1.1, 16.2, 2.1, oma=c(0,0,0,0), mar=c(0,0,0,0))
      text(cex=0.8, x=16.25, adj=c(0,0.5), y=seq(2.1,1.1,l=5), labels = seq(
        min(na.omit(pd$`n_roh>12`)),
        max(na.omit(pd$`n_roh>12`)),l=5))}
    }
    
    {if(input$pdColor=="mthap_haplocart"){
      plot(xlab="", ylab="", xaxt="n", yaxt="n", c(15.8,17), c(1.1,2.1), type = "n",
           axes=F)
      legend("topright", legend=names(color.mthap_haplocart),
             fill=color.mthap_haplocart, bty="n", cex = 1)
    }
    }
    
    {if(input$pdColor=="mthap_haplogrep"){
      
      plot(xlab="", ylab="", xaxt="n", yaxt="n", c(15.8,17), c(1.1,2.1), type = "n",
           axes=F)
      legend("topright", legend=names(color.mthap_haplogrep),
             fill=color.mthap_haplogrep, bty="n", cex = 1)
    }
    }
    
    {if(input$pdColor=="Ychr_HG_pathPfynder"){
      plot(xlab="", ylab="", xaxt="n", yaxt="n", c(2,20), c(0.5,2.9), type = "n",
           axes=F)
      legend("topright", legend=names(color.Ychr_HG_pathPfynder),
             fill=color.Ychr_HG_pathPfynder, bty="n", text.width = 10,
             cex = 1)
    }
    }
    
    
  })
}


ui <- tagList(
  
  # App title
  #titlePanel("Namu site"),
  
  
  # Define tabs:
  navbarPage("Namu",
             
             # TAB 1______________________________________________
             tabPanel("Site",
                      # Sidebar panel for inputs __________________
                      sidebarPanel(width=2,
                                   
                                   # Input: Selector for variables
                                   selectInput("Genetic_Sex", label = "Genetic_Sex",
                                               choices=as.character(df.achaeo$Genetic_Sex),
                                               selected=as.character(df.achaeo$Genetic_Sex),
                                               multiple=T, width=120),
                                   selectInput("ID.genetic", label = "ID.genetic",
